1
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:21,900
[Underground of Soul-Cleansing Temple]

2
00:01:26,039 --> 00:01:27,039
Why did you call me back?

3
00:01:27,039 --> 00:01:28,840
Do you know what I was just doing?

4
00:01:29,140 --> 00:01:30,430
Who cares?

5
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:36,620
Shrimpie appeared just now.

6
00:01:37,259 --> 00:01:38,160
I was waiting for him there.

7
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:39,690
Do you know what he did?

8
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:41,090
How would I know?

9
00:01:41,090 --> 00:01:43,289
Stop pretending. You know everything.

10
00:01:43,590 --> 00:01:44,920
You've known all along.

11
00:01:45,509 --> 00:01:46,979
How long are you going to lie to me?

12
00:01:46,979 --> 00:01:47,770
It's been 10 years!

13
00:01:47,770 --> 00:01:48,979
Do you still think
I'm the same as 10 years ago,

14
00:01:48,979 --> 00:01:50,150
doing whatever you tell me to do?

15
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:50,870
Sit down!

16
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:56,650
But I won't listen to
another word from you.

17
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:00,510
Zhang Haixia.

18
00:02:02,010 --> 00:02:04,700
killed everyone in the priest's mansion.

19
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,930
He even hung Priest Su Ya's body

20
00:02:06,930 --> 00:02:08,240
on the water cart

21
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,979
just to avenge us.

22
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:13,670
Do you know he's completely lost his mind?

23
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:16,540
Didn't you see him
kill Great Golden Blade?

24
00:02:16,540 --> 00:02:18,010
Didn't you say that no matter what he did,

25
00:02:18,010 --> 00:02:18,740
you'd forgive him,

26
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:20,800
clean up his mess, and bring him home?

27
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:24,810
Where is he?

28
00:02:27,740 --> 00:02:29,340
Don't play this game with me.

29
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,620
What does this have to do with

30
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:32,220
you not telling me the truth?

31
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:44,290
The antidote Zhang Haixia used
is also a poison.

32
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:47,060
It will cause irreversible damage
to his mind.

33
00:02:47,460 --> 00:02:49,490
The agents who used this antidote before

34
00:02:49,490 --> 00:02:51,290
all went mad without exception.

35
00:02:51,460 --> 00:02:53,460
They went around attacking people/

36
00:02:53,930 --> 00:02:56,260
They couldn't control themselves at all.

37
00:03:00,810 --> 00:03:02,150
So I killed them all.

38
00:03:12,810 --> 00:03:14,070
He's already saved...

39
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:18,250
and you're only telling me this now?

40
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:21,290
Would it have changed anything
if I told you then?

41
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,380
If you knew, would you not have saved him?

42
00:03:31,410 --> 00:03:32,800
Besides, Zhang Haixia

43
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,530
carries clues about Mo Yungao.

44
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:38,420
It concerns
the safety of countless people.

45
00:03:39,530 --> 00:03:41,390
Even if you didn't choose to do so,

46
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:43,810
he had to live.

47
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,570
You could have told me earlier.

48
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:15,500
You and he both hid it from me.

49
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:17,510
Was it for my own good?

50
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,490
Have you ever considered my feelings?

51
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:26,660
Well, now you know.

52
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:30,060
If I asked you to kill him,

53
00:04:30,930 --> 00:04:32,150
could you do it?

54
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:50,460
Then I have to at least talk to him once.

55
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:53,500
He might have even shown up just now.

56
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:55,300
Why on earth did you call me back?

57
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:03,060
Got me to come back

58
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:04,920
just to make me clean a darn pond.

59
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,070
Keeping everything from me,

60
00:05:07,070 --> 00:05:08,470
not telling me anything.

61
00:05:08,930 --> 00:05:10,530
Am I not part of the Archives?

62
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:13,400
Now making me some bullshit Director.

63
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,460
Be it yourself in your coffin.

64
00:05:16,330 --> 00:05:17,750
Priest Su Ya of Bailejing

65
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,350
died of illness previously.

66
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:22,020
Someone brought him back to life.

67
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,920
But after a few years,

68
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,680
his temperament
suddenly changed drastically.

69
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,740
Originally an honest and gentle man,

70
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:29,380
he became bloodthirsty.

71
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:30,920
If the Priest Su Ya's condition

72
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,710
is the same as Zhang Haixia's,

73
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:35,830
yet he could maintain
his original state for years,

74
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:38,090
it means he has a way to restrain himself.

75
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,360
Perhaps deep in Bailejing,

76
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:42,880
there is a way to save Zhang Haixia.

77
00:05:50,330 --> 00:05:51,130
Mentor.

78
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,840
Is it possible that
Priest Su Ya was saved by chief?

79
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:57,270
Also, if he can cure your illness,

80
00:05:57,270 --> 00:05:58,740
can he also cure Shrimpie?

81
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:01,310
Maybe.

82
00:06:05,370 --> 00:06:07,220
Don't think about
looking for Zhang Haixia.

83
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:08,950
He is no longer who he used to be.

84
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,980
If you can't realize this,

85
00:06:10,980 --> 00:06:12,740
then it's best you two don't meet.

86
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:14,160
He is crazy, not stupid.

87
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,160
He hasn't forgotten us.

88
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,960
Zhang Hailou, think carefully.

89
00:06:17,370 --> 00:06:19,420
Zhang Haixia killed Priest Su Ya

90
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:20,980
and let you see it,
but didn't come to see you—

91
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:21,600
why?

92
00:06:27,330 --> 00:06:28,860
He's checking my reaction.

93
00:06:35,810 --> 00:06:37,580
Why did he kill so many people?

94
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:40,930
Zhang Haixia
is an incredibly smart person.

95
00:06:40,930 --> 00:06:42,170
If he wants to do evil,

96
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:44,600
even I don't have the confidence
to stop him.

97
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,250
Do you know

98
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:46,310
how terrifying the person

99
00:06:46,310 --> 00:06:47,840
you have to deal with now is?

100
00:06:49,130 --> 00:06:50,750
You'd better calm down.

101
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:53,020
Otherwise, just like before,

102
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:55,070
you'll do something you regret.

103
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:37,510
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

104
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:40,419
[Episode 27]

105
00:08:56,310 --> 00:08:58,150
[Soul-Cleansing Temple]

106
00:09:09,940 --> 00:09:10,770
You're back.

107
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,310
I told my sister.

108
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,960
I'm going to kill Mo Yungao

109
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,820
to avenge my family and brothers.

110
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:18,220
That's up to you.

111
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,090
I will also kill Zhang Haixia.

112
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:24,970
Is that up to me too?

113
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:30,230
With the way he is now,

114
00:09:30,530 --> 00:09:32,010
it's hard for anyone to kill him.

115
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:33,050
If you want to get yourself killed,

116
00:09:33,050 --> 00:09:34,250
I don't mind one more.

117
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:54,670
Shrimpie.

118
00:09:56,530 --> 00:09:57,590
If you want to play,

119
00:09:59,370 --> 00:10:00,430
I'll play with you.

120
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:56,550
Little Taoist, you're quite good at this.

121
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:58,550
Is this how you used to pursue girls?

122
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,580
Why are your ears red?

123
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:10,630
Don't tell me...

124
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:15,010
you're still a virgin?

125
00:11:22,630 --> 00:11:24,230
I know you're feeling awful.

126
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:25,860
I also know

127
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,030
you're like this because you lost

128
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:29,430
your family and friends.

129
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,330
But you still need to cherish your life

130
00:11:33,220 --> 00:11:34,530
and not hurt yourself.

131
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:36,770
Or...

132
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:40,400
their deaths would be in vain.

133
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:44,790
Darn Taoist,

134
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:45,980
you're still wet behind the ears!

135
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:48,040
Stop acting all highly in front of me!

136
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:50,580
That darn Taoist.

137
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:53,040
He's obviously experienced nothing

138
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:55,670
yet preach such big principles.

139
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:07,480
I need to teach you a lesson.

140
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:18,680
You're right.

141
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,880
My friends are dead,

142
00:12:20,940 --> 00:12:22,000
and my family is dead too.

143
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:22,820
Now,

144
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:25,250
I'm the only one left in this world.

145
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:27,530
Come and sit down.

146
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:30,280
My life's so tough I might as well die.

147
00:12:36,340 --> 00:12:37,220
How am I

148
00:12:38,010 --> 00:12:39,440
supposed to live?

149
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:44,050
Actually,

150
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,820
it's normal to feel pain.

151
00:12:46,820 --> 00:12:48,960
But I'm in too much pain.

152
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:50,010
I understand.

153
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:51,450
Drink a little with me.

154
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:52,080
I...

155
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:04,240
I know why you want revenge.

156
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:07,650
It's not for justice,

157
00:13:07,790 --> 00:13:10,290
it's to ease the pain in your heart.

158
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:13,580
But let me tell you about revenge,

159
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:14,860
-it isn't...
-Shut up!

160
00:13:29,390 --> 00:13:29,910
What...

161
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:31,560
What are you doing?

162
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:34,490
I've taken a fancy to you today.

163
00:13:44,770 --> 00:13:46,020
[Soul-Cleansing Temple]

164
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:54,490
[Soul-Cleansing Temple]

165
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:38,890
Robbery.

166
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:39,760
Robbery?

167
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,600
-I have no money.
-I don’t want your money.

168
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:42,580
I want this.

169
00:14:43,630 --> 00:14:45,300
You want... manure?

170
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:46,290
Go.

171
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:03,980
The dung cart!

172
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:05,240
My dung cart!

173
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,370
Zhang Hailou, Zhang Hailou.

174
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:50,460
Wh-Why...

175
00:15:50,460 --> 00:15:51,390
Why are you here?

176
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,240
That's not how

177
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,910
you sounded like last night.

178
00:15:57,340 --> 00:15:58,550
Last night...

179
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:02,340
What did you give me to drink last night?

180
00:16:02,340 --> 00:16:03,050
Liquor.

181
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:05,390
Get ready to go.

182
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,260
The women of Phoenix Fortress

183
00:16:12,370 --> 00:16:13,370
are all mantises.

184
00:16:13,470 --> 00:16:15,730
They'll eat you after sleeping with you.

185
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:17,340
Close your mouth.

186
00:16:17,340 --> 00:16:18,340
Hurry up and pack.

187
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:19,940
We're leaving for Bone-Washing Cave.

188
00:16:19,940 --> 00:16:22,000
Your mentor and my mentor can't wait.

189
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:30,110
We are top-tier wanted criminals now.

190
00:16:30,650 --> 00:16:32,250
We need to keep a low profile.

191
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:11,410
[Soul-Cleansing Temple]

192
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,490
You prepared the crate?

193
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:42,110
How could you have
predicted everything so precisely?

194
00:17:42,110 --> 00:17:43,700
If you ever get into trouble,

195
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:44,760
take 3 steps back.

196
00:17:45,110 --> 00:17:48,370
I'll be right behind you
to ensure you have a fallback plan.

197
00:17:49,810 --> 00:17:51,180
No matter what happens,

198
00:17:51,290 --> 00:17:53,490
you'll leave a fallback plan
for me too,

199
00:17:56,660 --> 00:17:57,520
right, Hailou?

200
00:17:57,900 --> 00:18:00,360
[Soul-Cleansing Temple]

201
00:18:04,050 --> 00:18:04,680
Brother!

202
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,000
Let's go look over there!

203
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,200
All right. Don't run!

204
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:12,220
Brother, this way.

205
00:18:12,370 --> 00:18:13,360
Slowly.

206
00:18:14,140 --> 00:18:16,270
You went crazy the moment you came out.

207
00:18:18,460 --> 00:18:20,190
Why are you still following us?

208
00:18:20,570 --> 00:18:22,330
Didn't I tell you I want revenge?

209
00:18:22,330 --> 00:18:24,100
Since you know Zhang Haixia,

210
00:18:22,610 --> 00:18:26,440
[General Store]

211
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,330
by following you,

212
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,850
I will definitely be able to find him.

213
00:18:26,850 --> 00:18:28,250
You are overthinking it.

214
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,820
He won't follow us anymore.

215
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:31,860
[Wanted]

216
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:34,530
Also,

217
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:36,030
don't expect us to help you

218
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:37,280
deal with Mo Yungao.

219
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:40,510
I am trying to save my mentor now
and have no time to deal with him.

220
00:18:40,510 --> 00:18:41,310
I'd like a piece.

221
00:18:41,310 --> 00:18:42,220
Okay, sir.

222
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:43,770
Did I ask you?

223
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:45,500
Don't flatter yourself.

224
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:52,220
Why does Bailejing
have festivals every day?

225
00:18:52,220 --> 00:18:53,660
And different ones too?

226
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:55,900
Besides, why does everyone

227
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,720
seem to have no reaction
to the death of the priest?

228
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:59,970
Didn't you hear about
the new priest?

229
00:19:00,250 --> 00:19:01,880
Priest Su Ji took office

230
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:03,830
-and is now the High Priest of Bailejing.
-The mountain bride is getting married!

231
00:19:03,830 --> 00:19:05,220
-Priest Su Ji...
-The mountain bride is getting married!

232
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:07,330
-Is the younger brother of Priest Su Ya.
-The mountain bride is getting married!

233
00:19:07,330 --> 00:19:09,530
The mountain bride is getting married!

234
00:19:12,980 --> 00:19:15,240
This must be the Bone-Washing Ceremony.

235
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:18,810
These people are here to wash their bones?

236
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:23,300
It's the Bone-Washing Ceremony,

237
00:19:23,310 --> 00:19:27,040
yet this kid is shouting about
the mountain bride getting married.

238
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:28,300
Ma'am.

239
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:31,110
Aren't people here to wash their bones?

240
00:19:31,110 --> 00:19:33,830
But I just heard someone shouting about
the mountain bride getting married.

241
00:19:33,830 --> 00:19:35,960
They're both happening today.

242
00:19:36,980 --> 00:19:38,980
The marriage and the bone-washing?

243
00:19:51,180 --> 00:19:51,610
Here.

244
00:19:56,330 --> 00:19:56,900
Ma'am.

245
00:19:58,640 --> 00:19:59,850
Why is it you again?

246
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:01,140
First time strangers, second time friends.

247
00:20:01,140 --> 00:20:02,440
Ma'am, let me ask you,

248
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,030
what are these people doing?

249
00:20:04,030 --> 00:20:05,640
Why are everyone leaving after placing

250
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:06,830
their bone urns here?

251
00:20:06,830 --> 00:20:08,350
Aren't they supposed to go wash the bones?

252
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:10,510
People here don't go to wash the bones.

253
00:20:10,510 --> 00:20:12,940
The bridal procession for
the mountain bride will go on our behalf.

254
00:20:12,940 --> 00:20:13,800
On your behalf?

255
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:15,180
You don't go in person?

256
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:16,000
In the past,

257
00:20:16,030 --> 00:20:17,750
we would go to wash the bones ourselves.

258
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:19,270
But this year the priest said

259
00:20:19,270 --> 00:20:20,570
to let the mountain bride's procession

260
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:21,470
go for us.

261
00:20:21,850 --> 00:20:23,290
The girl to be sent to the mountain

262
00:20:23,290 --> 00:20:25,030
is to be the wife
of our Bailejing's guardian deity,

263
00:20:25,030 --> 00:20:26,410
Feikun Balu.

264
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,290
Letting her wash the bones on our behalf

265
00:20:28,290 --> 00:20:30,630
will allow our loved ones
to rest in peace.

266
00:20:31,530 --> 00:20:32,250
Thank you.

267
00:20:32,530 --> 00:20:34,000
Excuse me.

268
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,420
Can I go in together with my mentor

269
00:20:35,420 --> 00:20:36,140
later?

270
00:20:36,140 --> 00:20:36,530
No.

271
00:20:36,530 --> 00:20:36,920
No.

272
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:38,250
No.

273
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:38,900
Huh?

274
00:20:40,380 --> 00:20:42,250
Didn't we agree to go to Bone-Washing Cave
to find the chief?

275
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,450
Why can my mentor only go by himself now?

276
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:45,830
What does this mean?

277
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:48,590
They are collecting bones now.

278
00:20:48,590 --> 00:20:50,250
The ceremony is later, right?

279
00:20:51,610 --> 00:20:52,580
Scatter first.

280
00:20:52,740 --> 00:20:56,400
Then find a chance to sneak
into the mountain bride's procession.

281
00:21:00,740 --> 00:21:01,420
Thank you.

282
00:21:15,810 --> 00:21:16,770
I'll follow first.

283
00:21:16,770 --> 00:21:18,630
You guys find a chance to sneak in.

284
00:21:20,610 --> 00:21:21,790
I'll follow her first.

285
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:23,650
You guys find a chance to sneak in.

286
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:34,440
Fabrics for sale!

287
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,640
Come and take a look.

288
00:21:36,090 --> 00:21:37,950
Many patterns and pretty styles.

289
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:39,350
We have all kinds.

290
00:21:40,830 --> 00:21:42,200
This fabric is really good.

291
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,440
Miss, come take a look.

292
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:44,480
Our new fabrics

293
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,880
will suit you perfectly.

294
00:21:46,330 --> 00:21:47,400
You have great taste, miss.

295
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:48,980
This fabric suits you very well.

296
00:21:48,980 --> 00:21:51,240
You'll definitely look beautiful in it.

297
00:22:01,330 --> 00:22:01,740
I...

298
00:22:08,270 --> 00:22:09,480
Do you like me?

299
00:22:19,650 --> 00:22:20,280
I...

300
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:26,100
If I asked you
to take responsibility for me,

301
00:22:29,180 --> 00:22:30,240
would you marry me?

302
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:44,220
I knew it. You're a hypocrite.

303
00:22:45,530 --> 00:22:46,270
I will!

304
00:22:51,050 --> 00:22:51,830
What did you say?

305
00:22:51,830 --> 00:22:52,440
I said,

306
00:22:52,590 --> 00:22:53,770
I will marry you.

307
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:54,900
I will take care of you.

308
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:58,560
I am willing to take responsibility
for you for the rest of my life.

309
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:16,060
♪ The past fades into traces on the page ♪

310
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:13,340
The rest of your life?

311
00:23:14,510 --> 00:23:16,570
We've only known each other for a day.

312
00:23:17,270 --> 00:23:22,980
♪ A silent breeze
brushes past that lingering warmth ♪

313
00:23:17,750 --> 00:23:18,570
Besides,

314
00:23:19,110 --> 00:23:20,500
who would marry a

315
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:22,700
poor Taoist who only lives on a mountain?

316
00:23:22,700 --> 00:23:23,760
I was tricking you.

317
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:30,240
♪ In this fleeting world,
I long for a moment of vivid life ♪

318
00:23:31,390 --> 00:23:35,960
♪ I may have a chance to open a door ♪

319
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:36,100
You didn't really think
I liked you, did you?

320
00:23:37,460 --> 00:23:43,930
♪ Where love and wish
meet in a fleeting moment ♪

321
00:23:44,730 --> 00:23:50,880
♪ There's no need to ask questions
in the maze ♪

322
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:49,850
I'm leaving. Don't follow me.

323
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:53,860
♪ The world's bustle ♪

324
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:59,350
♪ Can briefly warm those
under a shared roof ♪

325
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:01,070
Slowly.

326
00:24:00,430 --> 00:24:06,120
♪ And the story has come to an end ♪

327
00:24:01,070 --> 00:24:02,800
Watch out for the people ahead.

328
00:24:04,180 --> 00:24:05,980
This chief really knows how to enjoy life.

329
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,770
This girl is quite pretty.

330
00:24:09,570 --> 00:24:10,880
What are you looking at?

331
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:13,080
This is the central stall of the street.

332
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:16,600
The mountain bride procession
will definitely pass by here.

333
00:24:23,980 --> 00:24:25,240
This one looks quite nice.

334
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:25,640
It should—

335
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:27,790
Do you really think
we're here for shopping?

336
00:24:27,790 --> 00:24:29,220
It should suit me.

337
00:24:29,850 --> 00:24:31,510
Why don't you help me put it on?

338
00:24:38,050 --> 00:24:39,850
I can't beat him up in the street.

339
00:24:43,330 --> 00:24:43,850
Done.

340
00:24:44,830 --> 00:24:45,440
All right.

341
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,170
I'll take it.

342
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:48,310
Thank you.

343
00:24:50,610 --> 00:24:51,740
Want some barbecue?

344
00:24:54,980 --> 00:24:56,110
That's my disciple.

345
00:24:56,220 --> 00:24:56,950
My disciple.

346
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,400
I taught him well.

347
00:24:59,000 --> 00:24:59,570
I taught him well.

348
00:24:59,570 --> 00:25:00,170
All right.

349
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:01,570
Have a taste.

350
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:04,590
Have one?

351
00:25:24,010 --> 00:25:24,610
It's good.

352
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:57,440
Why does this bride's wedding dress

353
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:58,880
look so familiar?

354
00:25:59,370 --> 00:26:00,800
[Yue Shu, the bride]

355
00:26:03,510 --> 00:26:04,090
Wanduo?

356
00:26:06,050 --> 00:26:08,450
So Wanduo is going to be
the mountain bride.

357
00:26:08,660 --> 00:26:10,920
What's the deal with the mountain bride?

358
00:26:11,090 --> 00:26:13,290
Why turn them into something like this?

359
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:16,190
Hey!

360
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:23,370
Miss, this doesn't feel right.

361
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:26,280
Save me!

362
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:28,220
The bride is being snatched!

363
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:29,200
Somebody come quick!

364
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:29,850
The bride is being snatched!

365
00:26:29,850 --> 00:26:30,650
Hurry!

366
00:26:30,980 --> 00:26:33,490
The bride has been snatched away!

367
00:26:48,830 --> 00:26:49,700
What did you do?

368
00:26:49,700 --> 00:26:51,220
We haven't even been here
for even an hour.

369
00:26:51,220 --> 00:26:52,290
I didn't do anything.

370
00:26:52,290 --> 00:26:53,350
All I did was act a little vain

371
00:26:53,350 --> 00:26:55,010
and put on a silver accessory.

372
00:26:58,750 --> 00:26:59,160
Hurry!

373
00:26:59,770 --> 00:27:00,270
Quick!

374
00:27:00,610 --> 00:27:01,160
Hurry!

375
00:27:01,350 --> 00:27:01,900
Let's go!

376
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:07,790
Sir,

377
00:27:08,830 --> 00:27:10,770
did you see two men
looking like they were running away?

378
00:27:10,770 --> 00:27:11,610
What?

379
00:27:12,290 --> 00:27:13,150
He's asking you

380
00:27:13,270 --> 00:27:14,700
if you have you seen two men—

381
00:27:14,700 --> 00:27:15,850
one looking like a Taoist priest

382
00:27:15,850 --> 00:27:16,880
and one pretty boy?

383
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:18,140
Nope, didn't see them.

384
00:27:18,140 --> 00:27:18,800
I'm busy.

385
00:27:18,980 --> 00:27:20,310
Go away.

386
00:27:23,010 --> 00:27:24,610
Did they go to the other side?

387
00:27:26,010 --> 00:27:27,710
We can't cross with weapons.

388
00:27:30,250 --> 00:27:32,110
This side of the river
is called Balianjie.

389
00:27:32,110 --> 00:27:33,630
The authorities
on both sides don't get along.

390
00:27:33,630 --> 00:27:34,850
They are carrying swords,

391
00:27:34,850 --> 00:27:36,330
so they definitely wouldn't dare go there.

392
00:27:36,330 --> 00:27:37,190
Why don't we...

393
00:27:37,510 --> 00:27:39,000
go hide on the other side of the river?

394
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:39,530
Let's go.

395
00:27:42,830 --> 00:27:43,350
If we

396
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:44,900
stay here,

397
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:46,700
can Feng Huang and Madam find us?

398
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:48,480
My mentor gets away quickly.

399
00:27:48,740 --> 00:27:49,440
Anyway, we have to

400
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:51,100
meet up at Bone-Washing Cave.

401
00:27:51,270 --> 00:27:52,870
We shouldn't worry too much.

402
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:57,660
What's the deal with that bride?

403
00:27:57,660 --> 00:27:58,640
Do you know her?

404
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:00,480
No.

405
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:02,440
It was after seeing my tattoo

406
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:04,370
that she stopped to ask me for help.

407
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:05,700
What tattoo?

408
00:28:06,090 --> 00:28:08,550
My tattoo is quite special.
It's right here.

409
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:10,740
The girl recognized it at a glance

410
00:28:10,740 --> 00:28:11,800
and asked for help.

411
00:28:12,070 --> 00:28:14,130
It means she is very familiar with us.

412
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:15,940
You are also from the Zhang family.

413
00:28:15,940 --> 00:28:17,740
Do you know much about the chief?

414
00:28:18,090 --> 00:28:18,750
What about?

415
00:28:18,750 --> 00:28:19,350
The chief

416
00:28:20,310 --> 00:28:21,440
has a similar tattoo

417
00:28:21,460 --> 00:28:22,740
right here.

418
00:28:23,050 --> 00:28:24,420
We are newcomers here.

419
00:28:25,250 --> 00:28:27,050
If the people here know about this tattoo,

420
00:28:27,050 --> 00:28:28,710
the chief must have told them.

421
00:28:29,590 --> 00:28:30,960
But why would the chief tell someone

422
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,760
about this tattoo for no reason?

423
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:35,470
Their relationship must be
beyond ordinary.

424
00:28:35,810 --> 00:28:36,500
Or perhaps,

425
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:39,020
she saw the tattoo, and he had to

426
00:28:39,220 --> 00:28:40,330
explain it to her.

427
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:44,850
See, that relationship
is even more unusual.

428
00:28:44,850 --> 00:28:47,380
He must have said it
when they were going at it.

429
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:50,440
Going at what?

430
00:28:51,250 --> 00:28:52,110
Consummation.

431
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,070
What are you saying?

432
00:28:56,070 --> 00:28:58,400
How could the chief
be that kind of person?

433
00:28:59,160 --> 00:29:00,440
Do you know him well?

434
00:29:02,310 --> 00:29:03,180
This chief,

435
00:29:03,180 --> 00:29:05,310
I heard he is apathetic.

436
00:29:06,010 --> 00:29:07,140
Let alone romance,

437
00:29:07,140 --> 00:29:08,140
he barely even eats.

438
00:29:08,140 --> 00:29:09,610
He has an eccentric temperament—
who'd have thought?

439
00:29:09,610 --> 00:29:11,000
After moving to Nanqiang
to live in seclusion,

440
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,200
he would actually...

441
00:29:12,810 --> 00:29:14,670
talk to someone about his tattoo?

442
00:29:14,900 --> 00:29:16,050
But this place is quite lively,

443
00:29:16,050 --> 00:29:17,900
and that girl is absolutely gorgeous.

444
00:29:17,900 --> 00:29:19,090
The chief sure has good taste.

445
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:20,370
He acts like a wild man.

446
00:29:21,850 --> 00:29:22,980
The most outrageous thing

447
00:29:22,980 --> 00:29:25,220
she asked for my help
when she was

448
00:29:25,420 --> 00:29:26,850
on her way to getting married.

449
00:29:26,850 --> 00:29:27,980
What does this mean?

450
00:29:28,140 --> 00:29:31,010
It means it wasn't the chief
she was getting married to.

451
00:29:31,010 --> 00:29:32,740
It seems there's something up
with Feikun Balu.

452
00:29:32,740 --> 00:29:33,490
Whatever.

453
00:29:34,180 --> 00:29:35,590
Since she's the chief's woman,

454
00:29:35,590 --> 00:29:36,850
she must be protected.

455
00:29:37,090 --> 00:29:39,220
She should have clues
about the chief.

456
00:29:39,590 --> 00:29:41,090
We can also take the chance to figure out,

457
00:29:41,090 --> 00:29:43,220
what this mountain bride is all about.

458
00:29:43,740 --> 00:29:44,270
Let's go.

459
00:29:46,510 --> 00:29:48,170
I have no money to pay the bill.

460
00:29:48,980 --> 00:29:50,110
You're out of money?

461
00:29:58,630 --> 00:29:59,220
Let's go.

462
00:30:06,570 --> 00:30:07,140
Sir.

463
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:08,840
Have you seen two men?

464
00:30:08,980 --> 00:30:11,220
One looks like a Taoist priest,
the other a pretty boy?

465
00:30:11,220 --> 00:30:12,250
No, no.

466
00:30:17,330 --> 00:30:18,460
Go ask someone else.

467
00:30:18,720 --> 00:30:19,250
Let's go.

468
00:30:25,400 --> 00:30:26,010
Sir.

469
00:30:26,900 --> 00:30:27,830
Have you seen

470
00:30:27,830 --> 00:30:29,240
an outsider with a beast tattoo?

471
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,370
A tattoo right here.

472
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:39,600
What about him?

